<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN CXIV. Soma Pavamana.</h3>  
<p>1. THE man who waIketh as the Laws of Indu Pavamana bid,&#151;<br> Men call him rich in children, him, O Soma, who hath met thy thought. Flow, Indu, flow for Indra's sake.<br> 2 Kasyapa, &#7770;&#7779;i, lifting up thy voice with hymn-composers' lauds,<br> Pav reverence to King Soma born the Sovran Ruler of the plants. Flow, Indu, flow for Indra's sake.<br> 3 Seven regions have their several Suns; the ministering priests are seven;<br> Seven are the &#256;ditya Deities,&#151;with these, O Soma, guard thou us. Flow, Indu, flow for Indra's sake.<br> 4 Guard us with this oblation which, King Soma, hath been dressed for thee.</p>  
<p></p>  
